one year ago today I had a mental breakdown 🫠

i remember laying on my floor for over 12 hours unable to move, crying, drool dripping down my face as I lay on the ground, my brain totally fried. my body was crashing. my mind was crashing. and I was beyond a hot mess. the back to back surprise pregnancies, my traumatic postpartum eclampsia, and the overwhelming stress of having Irish twins on top of having four kids in five years, became too much for me to handle.

that day one year ago began an INCREDIBLE healing journey in my life. healing my body. healing my soul. healing my mind. and God POURING revelation upon me like I’ve never experienced. this has been one of the best years of my life because of the incredible amount of healing + growth I’ve walked through. 

as I think of where I was one year ago to today, I can hardly believe the person I once was. I am so thankful to God for all He has done, and I’m extremely excited to see how He will continue to grow me. 

if you’re in a hard season, hold tight friend. you can be on the brink of the greatest turning point in your life 💙

the BEST way to teach toddlers to obey, is boundaries.

what does this practically mean for a toddler? giving them two options, and IMMEDIATELY following through on one of those options. 

EXAMPLES:
“Would you like to walk to the car or would you like mommy to carry you?” then IMMEDIATE follow through 

“Would you like to put on your jacket or would you like mommy to help you put on your jacket? then IMMEDIATE follow through. 

✨really it’s giving your child two options that will make you happy either way. 

THIS HAS BEEN A GAME CHANGER FOR MY KIDS! with my first two kids I started implementing this so much later in their lives, but by my third child I was using these tools by a year old, and he immediately started understanding the concept, and obeying what I would ask him to do!
